//TOPIC: Border Radius --

(Property: border-radius)
border-radius is used to round the corners of an element.

//HEADING: Individual properties: --

border-top-left-radius
border-top-right-radius
border-bottom-right-radius
border-bottom-left-radius

//HEADING: Shorthand rules: --

1 value → all corners same
2 values → top corners | bottom corners
3 values → top-left | top-right & bottom-right | bottom-left
4 values → top-left | top-right | bottom-right | bottom-left


//HEADING: Shorthand Cases --

//HEADING: 1️⃣ One Value --
border-radius: 10px;

✔ All corners = 10px

//HEADING: 2️⃣ Two Values --
border-radius: 10px 20px;

✔ Top Left & Top Right = 10px
✔ Bottom Right & Bottom Left = 20px

//HEADING: 3️⃣ Three Values --
border-radius: 10px 20px 30px;

✔ Top Left = 10px
✔ Top Right & Bottom Right = 20px
✔ Bottom Left = 30px

//HEADING: 4️⃣ Four Values --
border-radius: 10px 20px 30px 40px;

✔ Top Left = 10px
✔ Top Right = 20px
✔ Bottom Right = 30px
✔ Bottom Left = 40px